1. Power Supply
	•	Input: 5V DC via USB-C connector
	•	Regulators:
	•	AMS1117-3.3 for 3.3V rail
	•	AMS1117-3.0 for 3.0V rail (GNSS module)
	•	Protection:
	•	Schottky diode for reverse polarity protection
	•	Polyfuse for overcurrent protection ￼ ￼ ￼

2. Microcontroller Unit (MCU)
	•	STM32F103C8T6:
	•	Powered by 3.3V
	•	Key Pins:
	•	PA9 (TX) / PA10 (RX): UART for GNSS
	•	PA5 (SCK), PA6 (MISO), PA7 (MOSI): SPI for display
	•	PA0: RPM sensor input
	•	PA1: Temperature sensor input
	•	PB0-PB3: Button inputs
	•	Programming Interface:
	•	SWD: SWDIO (PA13), SWCLK (PA14)

3. Display Interface
	•	2.4” TFT LCD:
	•	Interface: SPI
	•	Connections:
	•	SCK: PA5
	•	MOSI: PA7
	•	CS: PB12
	•	DC: PB13
	•	RESET: PB14
	•	Backlight Control: PB15
	•	Connector: Rear-mounted 20-pin FPC connector

4. GNSS Module Interface
	•	u-blox NEO-6M:
	•	Power: 3.0V from AMS1117-3.0
	•	Communication: UART
	•	TX: Connected to MCU RX (PA10)
	•	RX: Connected to MCU TX (PA9)
	•	Connector: 4-pin JST for detachable connection ￼

5. Sensors
	•	RPM Sensor:
	•	Type: Hall effect sensor
	•	Connection: PA0
	•	Temperature Sensor:
	•	Type: Analog (e.g., LM35)
	•	Connection: PA1

6. User Interface
	•	Buttons:
	•	Four tactile buttons connected to PB0-PB3
	•	Pull-down resistors to ensure defined logic levels

7. USB Interface
	•	USB-C Connector:
	•	Purpose: Power input and optional USB communication
	•	Connections:
	•	VBUS: 5V input
	•	D+: Connected to MCU USB D+ (PA12)
	•	D-: Connected to MCU USB D- (PA11)
